title: Checksum comparison on incoming data from Multispeq device
message:
Checksum comparison on incoming data from Multispeq device

A CRC32 value is calculated and compared to the received checksum.
If they do not match, no data is plotted and a file is written to:
/sdcard/Photosynq/CRC/expected_X_received_X
E.g. expected_EA4E203D_received_BB8880BB

This file contains all data which was received via BLE since the last
correct checksum.

TODO: send this file via "Send debug" . On the other hand, we do not want
to clutter the Android device with too many files, so maybe just send
the last few files.
TODO: add a UI message such as a 'Toast' when there is a checksum error.

title: Preliminary version of Android vision for capturing barcodes
message:
Preliminary version of Android vision for capturing barcodes

Added a standalone activity for capturing barcodes. Taken from the
official googlesamples/android-vision repository. Note that the
CameraSource in package barcode has a slightly different implemenation
than CameraSource in Google's gms repository; specifically this
implementation allows to set flash and autofocus. If these features are
not needed, one could also use CameraSource from the official
repository.

title: Added test measurement for debugging
message:
Added test measurement for debugging

Copies html files from assets to 'external' storage (normally found under
/sdcard/Android/data/org.photosynq.android.photosynq). Then a webview is
shown when a new test measurement is completed. Note that the test
protocol sent to the device is hardcoded, as well as macros.js and
macros_variable.js. Only data.js is re-written with new values.

title: Added CommunicationEngine and test measurement
message:
Added CommunicationEngine and test measurement

Added CommunicationEngine.java for interpreting responses from the PhotoSynq
device. (Maybe there could be a more suitable name, but 'Protocol' is
already used elsewhere). Responses contain \r\n as line separators, and
a message is finished when \r\n\r\n is received. Note that for
displaying and storing these messages on the Android device, \r\n is
replaced by a single \n.

Added a button in bluetooth debug screen for a test measurement.
